<br>
At first I didn't much like this idea. But then I had one of my own. Probably not an original idea, but one that I don't particularly feel like searching for threads on.<br>
<br>
Idea: make our familiars nuke. No melee, just nuke. We might need 3 or 4 different kinds (fire cold magic stun). They should nuke at the wizards level for mob resist purposes.They should be able to nuke indefinitely, but not for large amounts, just enough that they approach the sustained DPS of the other classes pets.<br>
<br>
Because that's our problem now. If we arent going to be the masters of short duration high DPS fights, then we at least need some solution for sustained DPS like all the other classes have. And a nuking pet isnt totally out of our ....idiom. <br>
<br>
Of course that would mean we would have to have the annoying flappy hanging around.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jarnin>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Likes to wear<BR>Yoda Under-Roos</span><br>  Posts: 2517<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/4/02 3:53 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Idea </span><hr size=1> No thanks. I don't want a pet. Most wizards don't want a pet. Making our familiars nuke would do two things:<br>
<br>
1. They'd eventually gain aggro just like pets do now, and with their limited hitpoints, they'd get killed. That means we'd have to resummon them more often, which is something I really don't want to have to do.<br>
<br>
2. They'd piss off all the other pet classes because wizards were never designed to be a pet class.<br>
<br>
Oh, and by the way, they're not nerfing our ability to solo. They're making zones that they <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>tried</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to design for groups, unsoloable. There's a big difference.<br>
In my opinion, our ability to solo fine up to level 60 is good enough. We really shouldn't be able to solo all that well from 61-65, but we still can. From what I hear, we can solo quite well from 61-65. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Jarnin Fisheermann</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>57th Evoker</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&lt;Ring of Cobalt&gt;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Rallos Zek</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daamij>daamij</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 346<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/6/02 4:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Idea </span><hr size=1> /pet get lost <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=132459"> Daamij 58 Wizard </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=enoah35>Enoah35</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 264<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/7/02 1:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Pets</span><hr size=1> Considering that we are on Pure magic channeling class I doubt a pet would be usefull. 1st of all I know that other games can channel familiar that can do stuff. Altho our pet already has its use... its just more like a self buff rather than a pet tho :/ . 2nd If pets starts to nuke then we will probably draw more additional agro. Considering the fact that our nukes already provokes quite a few agro... additional agro won't be very desirable.<br>
<br>
I agree we wizards needs something that noone can do. I still think Shapeshifting ourselves to dragon is the best idea :P (still don't get why mages get shapeshifting to elementals and we not into drake or dragons :/)<br>
<br>
Enoah <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=luxum>Luxum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorceress<BR>Dark Elf Admirer</span><br>  Posts: 1201<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/7/02 8:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pets</span><hr size=1> If i had wanted a pet i'd have rolled a necro or a mage, thanks. <p>Luxum Aeturnum &lt;Cestus Dei&gt;<br>
