Veeshan</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=milaru00>Milaru 00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 845<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/7/02 8:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pets</span><hr size=1> first people ask for Dots, then bolts, then pets, my god, why play a wizard anymore. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gyorg@graffeswizardcompilation>Gyorg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/7/02 2:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> pets....nah</span><hr size=1> Yeah, I agree, I would rather have bigger/more efficient/faster casting/more accessible nukes than anything else.<br>
Sony just seems reluctant to give them to us for some reason.<br>
<br>
Other (better) ideas:<br>
- Something like E'Ci, but for Fire and Magic<br>
- A focus effect from the familiar, like maybe something that makes you cast as if you were a higher level, for resist and damage purposes. Or maybe an Evocation skill bonus (assuming that even does anything)<br>
- Make Telekin a Lure based stun with a small knockback, for spell interruption, and maybe make it not an all or nothing resist<br>
- Pointy Hats<br>
<br>
<br>
